companyName: iShares Edge MSCI Intl Quality Factor
description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI World ex USA Sector Neutral Quality Index.
 The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index measures the performance of international developed large- and mid-capitalization stocks exhibiting relatively higher quality characteristics as identified through three fundamental variables: return on equity, earnings variability and debt-to-equity.
